AGI - The Chief Prosecutor of the International Criminal Court (Cpi), Karim Khan, has asked the courts of the Hague court for arrest warrants for Israeli prime minister Benjamin Netanyahu and Hamas leader in Gaza, Yahya Sinwar> for war crimes and against humanity. Istanze was also advanced to Mohammed Deif, the leader of the Ezzedin Al Qassam Brigades, and Ismail Haniyeh, the leader of the Hamas political office, who together with Sinwar, are accused of "termination, murder, hostages, rape and sexual violence during detention."
&nbsp;
In Khan's view, Israeli Defense Minister Yoav Gallant, who, like Netanyahu, is accused of "having caused the extermination, caused by hunger as a method of war, including the denial of humanitarian aid, deliberately targeting civilians." The news unleashed the harsh reaction of the Jewish state, which condemned the equality between Netanyahu and Sinwar. "While the assassins and rapists of Hamas commit crimes against humanity against our brothers and sisters, the public ministry (di&nbsp; Cpi) at the same time cites the Israeli prime minister and defence minister together with the vile Nazi monsters of Hamas, a historical shame that will be remembered forever," said foreign minister Israel Katz.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
It is a "crime of historical proportions", said the minister of the war cabinet Benny Gantz, claiming that "trace a parallel between the leaders of a democratic country determined to defend itself from despicable terrorism and the leaders of a bloodthirsty terrorist organization is a profound distortion of justice and a blatant moral failure." Also for opposition leader Yair Lapid, "it is not possible to issue arrest warrants against Netanyahu, Sinwar and Deif. There is no such comparison, we cannot accept it and it is unforgivable >". "I expect the American administration to deliver arrest warrants. I think they'll support us," he added.
&nbsp;
On the same line, the Host Family Forum, which "respinned the symmetrical proposal between Israeli leaders and Hamas terrorists," underlines that "the way to show the world that the two are not the same is to immediately start a negotiation that will release the hostages." The request for arrest warrants for both Netanyahu and Sinwar also aroused indignation among the Palestinians: > for Wasel Abu Youssef, exponent of the Organization for the Liberation of Palestine (Olp), in this way "confusion between the victim and the executioner". "The International Criminal Court is required to issue arrest warrants against Israeli officials who continue to commit genocide crimes in the Gaza Strip," he added. In the same opinion, Hamas, convinced that Khan's decision "equipes the victim to the executioner" and encourages the continuation of the "extermination war". &nbsp;
&nbsp;
<h2>Amal Clooney is among the consultants of Khan</h2>
There is also Amal Alamuddin, wife of actor George Clooney > as international law lawyer, among experts of international law who have done a consultancy work for the attorney head of the International Criminal Court, Karim Khan.
The magistrate today presented to the Preliminary Chamber of the Cpi evidence justifying five arrest warrants against the high Israeli and Palestinian exponents. And the name of Amal is among those that Khan, at the conclusion of his request, cited as "precious consultants" of his work >.
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
Very accredited lawyer, Alamuddin after the wedding took the name of her husband, with whom she had two children. Lebanese with British citizenship, the lawyer specializes in international law and human rights; and teaches human rights at the Law School of Columbia University, the prestigious New York university campus where the pro-Palestinian protests began that later spread to universities around the world. Recently Amal Clooney had been criticized on social media > for never expressing what was happening in the Gaza Strip. But he obviously chose to move differently: instead of complaining to gossip, he wanted to find the legal bases to ask for international arrest warrants for war crimes, so much against the men of Hamas (as well as Sinwar, those in the 'politburo', Mohammed Deif and Ismail Haniyeh) than for those at the top of the Israeli government (as well as the Prime Minister of Defense Yoav Gallant).
